@Nomena and WNT fan:<br/>
Here's one to put in the hopper. How about a German (female) coach NOT named Silvia Neid? They have a very well developed (and well followed) Women's Bundesliga.<br/>
How about a French club coach?<br/><br/>Agree that Brazil has been hamstrung (for both the men and the women, really) by horrendous coaching, and the Italian women have been pretty much a non factor. As for the Italian Woman, Morace, who coached Canada, the players were ready to strike when the Canadian federation broached the idea of making a change, and Canada was done absolutely no favors by the draw for that tournament, and played Germany as well as anyone did until Japan sprung the upset.
